'''塞爾柱王朝'''（[[波斯語|波斯語]]： آل سلجوق，''Al-e Saljuq''）是中世纪时期由[[烏古斯人|乌古斯突厥人]]建立起的[[遜尼派|遜尼派]][[穆斯林|穆斯林]]王朝<ref>"''Turkish dynasty also spelled Seljuk ruling military family of the Oğuz (Ghuzz) Turkic tribes that invaded southwestern Asia in the 11th century and eventually founded an empire....''".[http://www.britannica.com/search?query=seljuq Encyclopedia Brittanica]</ref><ref>"''The Turkish groups of the greatest import in the history of Europe and W Asia were, however, the Seljuks and the Osmanli or Ottoman Turks, both members of the Oghuz confederations.''".[http://education.yahoo.com/reference/encyclopedia/entry/Turks Encyclopedia Columbia] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111231733/http://education.yahoo.com/reference/encyclopedia/entry/Turks |date=2013-11-11 }}</ref><ref>''Saljuqs'', Andrew Peacock, '''Encyclopaedia Iranica''', (May 25, 2010)."''A dynasty of Turkish origin that ruled much of Anatolia''".[http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/saljuqs-iii Encyclopedia Iranica]</ref>，后期王朝成員逐渐[[波斯文化|波斯化]]，为[[中世紀|中世紀]]时期西亚及中亞地區[[突厥-波斯文化|突厥-波斯文化]]的發展打下了基础<ref>Grousset, Rene, ''The Empire of the Steppes'', (Rutgers University Press, 1991), 161,164; "..renewed the Seljuk attempt to found a great Turko-Persian empire in eastern Iran..", "It is to be noted that the Seljuks, those Turkomans who became sultans of Persia, did not Turkify Persia-no doubt because they did not wish to do so. On the contrary, it was they who voluntarily became Persians and who, in the manner of the great old Sassanid kings, strove to protect the Iranian populations from the plundering of Ghuzz bands and save Iranian culture from the Turkoman menace."</ref><ref>Nishapuri, Zahir al-Din Nishapuri (2001), "The History of the Seljuq Turks from the Jami’ al-Tawarikh: An Ilkhanid Adaptation of the [[Saljuq-nama|Saljuq-nama]] of Zahir al-Din Nishapuri," Partial tr. K.A. Luther, ed. C.E. Bosworth, Richmond, UK.  K.A. Luther: "... the Turks were illiteratre and uncultivated when they arrived in Khurasan and had to depend on Iranian scribes, poets, jurists and theologians to man the institution of the Empire"(pg 9)</ref>。塞爾柱王朝曾建立[[塞尔柱帝国|大塞爾柱帝國]]以及[[魯姆蘇丹國|罗姆蘇丹國]]，統治區域東起[[波斯|波斯]]、西達[[安納托利亞|安納托利亞]]高原，王朝的擴張使安納托利亞、[[高加索|高加索]]等地[[突厥化|突厥化]]，也间接地引发了[[第一次十字軍東征|第一次十字軍東征]]。

==歷史==
塞爾柱人源自於[[突厥人|突厥]][[烏古斯人|烏古斯人]]分支<ref>Concise Britannica Online [http://concise.britannica.com/ebc/article-9378199/Seljuq-dynasty Seljuq Dynasty] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070114233201/http://concise.britannica.com/ebc/article-9378199/Seljuq-dynasty |date=2007-01-14 }} article</ref><ref>Merriam-Webster Online – Definition of [http://www.m-w.com/cgi-bin/dictionary?va=seljuk Seljuk]</ref><ref>The History of the Seljuq Turks: From the Jami Al-Tawarikh ([http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0700713425&id=jmMpaJZemk0C&pg=PA3&lpg=PA3&dq=%22Jami+Al-Tawarikh%22%2Bsaljuq%2Boghuz%2Bturks&sig=98_xadLFwNz0aimq-Yd6lwzdm30 LINK])</ref><ref>History of the Ottoman Empire and Modern Turkey – Stanford Shaw ([http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0521291631&id=UVmsI0P9RDUC&pg=PA7&lpg=PA7&dq=seljuk%2Bturkish%2Bturkoman%2Bturkomans&sig=Bgfb3GEfOrlabxfHSy27suztLNM LINK])</ref>，他們在9世紀生活於穆斯林世界邊緣，包含[[中亞|中亞]]的[[裏海|裏海]]北部和[[鹹海|鹹海]]、{{tsl|en|Kazakh Steppe|哈薩克草原}}、[[突厥斯坦|突厥斯坦]][[阿姆河|阿姆河]]畔等地。他們騎術精湛，周邊勢力常來此招募傭兵。[[波斯|波斯]]散文家{{tsl|en|Al-Jahiz|賈希茲}}形容他們：{{cquote|（突厥人）對手工藝或商業、醫學、幾何學、水果種植、建築、開鑿運河或稅務不感興趣，只喜歡劫掠、打獵、騎術、與敵對部族打小仗、掠奪戰利品、入侵其他國家。<ref name="CB"> {{Cite book | title = 劍橋插圖伊斯蘭世界史 | author =  Francis Robinson（ 法蘭西斯·魯賓遜 ）| others = 黃中憲譯 | location = 臺灣 | publisher = 如果出版社 | date = 2008 | ISBN = 9789866702198 }} </ref>}}

10世紀中期，由於[[加兹尼王国|加兹尼王国]]僱傭他們擔任[[河中地區|河中地區]]的警備，烏古斯人開始與周邊穆斯林城市密切往來。

10世紀末，塞爾柱人的領袖[[塞爾柱·貝格|塞爾柱·貝格]]與烏古斯人頭目[[葉護|葉護]]反目後，他率領部族移居於下[[錫爾河|錫爾河]]西岸（Jaxartes）。西元985年左右，塞爾柱人皈依了[[伊斯蘭教|伊斯蘭教]]<ref name = Adas>Michael Adas, ''Agricultural and Pastoral Societies in Ancient and Classical History'', (Temple University Press, 2001), 99.</ref>。

1025年，[[图格鲁勒·貝格|图格鲁勒·貝格]]，[[恰格勒·貝格|恰格勒·貝格]]兄弟和叔叔穆薩·優素福(Musa Yabghu)等人率領塞爾柱部族南遷進入波斯[[呼羅珊|呼羅珊]]省，協助[[喀喇汗國|喀喇汗國]]的王族[[阿里特勤|阿里特勤]]對抗加兹尼王族{{tsl|en|Muhammad of Ghazni|穆哈馬德}}的攻擊，1029年，貝格兄弟與阿里特勤發生爭執，同盟關係緊張，不過加兹尼此時也陷入內戰，是故戰端稍歇。

1030年，穆哈馬德的雙胞胎兄長{{tsl|en|Mas'ud I of Ghazni|馬蘇德一世}}結束內戰成為新蘇丹，他繼承了弟弟及父親[[加兹尼的马哈茂德|马哈茂德]]攻略河中地區的方針向北方施壓。1032年，{{tsl|en|Battle of Dabusiyya|達布西耶之戰}}爆發，貝格兄弟再次出兵協助阿里特勤，在喀喇汗軍與加兹尼軍互有損失的狀況下，兩軍協議各自退兵回國。

1035年，[[沙赫·馬立克|沙赫·馬立克]]在[[花剌子模|花剌子模]]擊敗貝格兄弟，南逃的兄弟向舊敵馬蘇德一世求援，馬蘇德一世斷然拒絕並派遣{{tsl|en|Begtoghdik|貝脫迪}}前去消滅對方，結果加兹尼軍大敗指揮官被俘，馬蘇德一世不得不割讓拿沙（Nasa）、法拉瓦（Farava）、大益等地給塞爾柱人。

1037年，图格鲁勒自封為蘇丹，並於隔年攻下加兹尼首都尼沙普爾。<ref>C.E. Bosworth, ''The Ghaznavids: 994-1040'', (Edinburgh University Press, 1963), 242.</ref><ref name="CB" />

1040年，衝突再次發生，塞爾柱人在[[丹丹納干戰役|丹丹納干戰役]]重創加兹尼軍隊<ref>Tony Jaques, ''Dictionary of Battles and Sieges: F-O'', (Greenwood Publishing Group, 2007), 476.</ref>，稍後，大塞爾柱帝國建立。帝國各地的原住民在接下來的幾十年中受到波斯文化影響，在宗教、語言以及風俗上被強制同化。<ref name="iranica">O.Özgündenli, ''"Persian Manuscripts in Ottoman and Modern Turkish Libraries"'', [[Encyclopaedia_Iranica|Encyclopaedia Iranica]], Online Edition, ([http://www.iranica.com/newsite/articles/ot_grp7/ot_pers_mss_ott_20050106.html LINK] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120122005207/http://www.iranica.com/newsite/articles/ot_grp7/ot_pers_mss_ott_20050106.html |date=2012-01-22 }})</ref><ref name="britannica">[[Encyclopædia_Britannica|Encyclopædia Britannica]], ''"Seljuq"'', Online Edition, ([http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9066688 LINK] {{Wayback|url=http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9066688 |date=20071219231803 }}): ''"... Because the Turkish Seljuqs had no Islamic tradition or strong literary heritage of their own, they adopted the cultural language of their Persian instructors in Islam. Literary Persian thus spread to the whole of Iran, and the Arabic language disappeared in that country except in works of religious scholarship ..."''</ref><ref name="Ravandi">M. Ravandi, ''"The Seljuq court at Konya and the Persianisation of Anatolian Cities"'', in Mesogeios (Mediterranean Studies), vol. 25–6 (2005), pp. 157–69</ref><ref>M.A. Amir-Moezzi, "Shahrbanu", [[Encyclopaedia_Iranica|Encyclopaedia Iranica]], Online Edition, ([http://www.iranica.com/newsite/articles/ot_grp7/ot_shahrbanu_20050131.html LINK] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070311062248/http://www.iranica.com/newsite/articles/ot_grp7/ot_shahrbanu_20050131.html |date=2007-03-11 }}): "... here one might bear in mind that Turco-Persian dynasties such as the Ghaznavids, Saljuqs and Ilkhanids were rapidly to adopt the Persian language and have their origins traced back to the ancient kings of Persia rather than to Turkish heroes or Muslim saints ..."</ref><ref>F. Daftary, ''Sectarian and National Movements in Iran, Khorasan, and Trasoxania during Umayyad and Early Abbasid Times'', in ''History of Civilizations of Central Asia'', Vol 4, pt. 1; edited by M.S. Asimov and [[Clifford_Edmund_Bosworth|C.E. Bosworth]]; [[UNESCO|UNESCO Publishing]], [[Institute_of_Ismaili_Studies|Institute of Ismaili Studies]]: "... Not only did the inhabitants of Khurasan not succumb to the language of the nomadic invaders, but they imposed their own tongue on them. The region could even assimilate the Turkic Ghaznavids and Seljuks (eleventh and twelfth centuries), the Timurids (fourteenth–fifteenth centuries), and the Qajars (nineteenth–twentieth centuries) ..."</ref>。

